  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation activities include a prospective hemolysis study conducted across five flow-speed combinations using a clinical-grade centrifugal pump; the study systematically recorded outlet hemolysis indices against varying impeller speeds and flow rates under standard perfusion conditions. The validation team notes that the observational study design captured representative in-vitro hemolysis behaviour across the full operating envelope and that these data serve as the primary empirical anchor for the CFD model predictions. The acceptance criterion RH < 1 was satisfied at all five operating points, and the study is cited throughout as providing controlled, well-characterised empirical evidence — a characterisation that implicitly equates the observational protocol with the controlled-experiment standard mandated by the binding requirement.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-verification-req-01",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-cfd-claim-01",
